 into warm, sterilised jars and seal immediately. Leave for a minimum of four weeks before using to allow flavours to develop."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Add chillies and garlic to the vegetable mixture for a spicier version.","Suggested vegetables: cauliflower, green beans, shallots or pearl onions, cucumber (deseeded), courgettes (deseeded), peppers, carrots.","Use unopened jars within 1 year.","An English interpretation of Indian chopped, pickled vegetables with spices. This homemade version is so much better than that you buy ready-made in a jar, and the best thing about it is you can use whatever vegetables you have to hand. Lovely served with a ploughman’s, cheese or cold meats, or a meat pie (try it with our game pie)."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","12h 35m","1 total recipe"]}